<subSubSection id="F4D30EAC53A19008E275F7BEBCF5659E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="typification">
<paragraph id="301AA23E4D4117F3D593AF4E6241C80D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Typification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C0D4C583578640E89405C21584DF1D80" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">None of the original syntypes in LE, K, M and S are very satisfactory, either lacking corollas or with badly eaten leaves. The lectotype selected here is probably the best from a not very high quality selection of specimens.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EB89F12997F1DD42FA00DC09E7DCF4A4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="D55931F858AA97F262079A0AEB1FFF27" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B81B47199C3373F9AED75E3A6D34802" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">This is a distinctive species because of the very lax inflorescence and the pendulous, yellow-green campanulate corollas which are abruptly inflated at the apex of the calyx.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
